====Usage notes====
A preceding comma may alter the meaning of a clause starting with a demonstrative adjective.  Compare the following sentences:
* ''Alle arbeiders die staken, zullen op sancties moeten rekenen.''
** All employees that strike, will have to count with sanctions. 
* ''Alle arbeiders, die staken, zullen op sancties moeten rekenen.''
** All employees, who strike, will have to count with sanctions.
In the first sentence, those employees that do not strike are safe.  In the second sentence, it is presupposed that all employees support the strike, and will all suffer under the sanctions.

